## Ruby Style

### Indentation & Spacing

```ruby
# Good: 2 spaces for indentation
def calculate_total
  items.sum do |item|
    item.price * item.quantity
  end
end

# Bad: 4 spaces or tabs
def calculate_total
    items.sum do |item|
        item.price * item.quantity
    end
end
```

**Rules:**
- Use 2 spaces for indentation (no tabs)
- One empty line between methods
- No trailing whitespace
- End files with a newline

### Line Length

```ruby
# Good: Under 120 characters
def long_method_name(parameter_one, parameter_two, parameter_three)
  # Method body
end

# If exceeds 120, break into multiple lines
def long_method_name(
  parameter_one,
  parameter_two,
  parameter_three
)
  # Method body
end
```

**Limit:** 120 characters per line (Rails default)

### Method Definitions

```ruby
# Good: Parentheses for methods with parameters
def calculate_total(items, tax_rate)
  subtotal = items.sum(&:price)
  subtotal * (1 + tax_rate)
end

# Good: No parentheses for methods without parameters
def total_count
  items.count
end

# Bad: Inconsistent parentheses
def calculate_total items, tax_rate  # Missing parentheses
end
```

### String Literals

```ruby
# Good: Double quotes for interpolation
name = "John"
message = "Hello, #{name}!"

# Good: Single quotes for static strings
status = 'active'
category = 'technology'

# Good: Heredoc for multi-line strings
sql = <<~SQL
  SELECT *
  FROM articles
  WHERE status = 'published'
SQL
```

### Blocks

```ruby
# Good: { } for single-line blocks
items.map { |item| item.name }

# Good: do...end for multi-line blocks
items.each do |item|
  puts item.name
  puts item.price
end

# Good: Use &: symbol-to-proc when possible
items.map(&:name)
items.select(&:active?)
```

### Hash Syntax

```ruby
# Good: Symbol keys with colon syntax
user = { name: 'John', email: 'john@example.com', age: 30 }

# Good: Rocket syntax for non-symbol keys
scores = { 'John' => 95, 'Jane' => 87 }

# Bad: Mixing styles
user = { :name => 'John', email: 'john@example.com' }  # Inconsistent
```

### Conditional Expressions

```ruby
# Good: Use && and || for boolean logic
if user.active? && user.verified?
  allow_access
end

# Good: unless for negative conditions (single condition only)
redirect_to login_path unless authenticated?

# Good: Ternary for simple conditions
status = published? ? 'Published' : 'Draft'

# Bad: unless with multiple conditions
unless user.inactive? || user.unverified?  # Confusing
  allow_access
end

# Bad: Nested ternaries
status = published? ? (featured? ? 'Featured' : 'Published') : 'Draft'  # Too complex
```

### Method Chaining

```ruby
# Good: One method per line for long chains
articles
  .published
  .recent
  .includes(:user, :category)
  .limit(10)

# Good: Single line for short chains
articles.published.recent

# Bad: Mixed formatting
articles.published
  .recent.includes(:user, :category)
  .limit(10)
```

